    <body>
        <h1>Chinese Pulao Recipe</h1>
            <p>1. Wash rice and soak for 20 minutes.
            2. Boil 4 cups water with a little salt.
            3. Add rice and cook until 90% done.
            4. Drain water and keep the rice aside.</p>
            <h3>2. Cook the Chicken</h3>
            <p>1. Heat oil in a pan.
            2. Add chopped garlic and fry until fragrant.
            3. Add chicken, salt, black pepper, and cook until chicken turns white.
            4. Add soya sauce, vinegar, and chicken cube (optional).
            5. Cook until chicken becomes tender.
            .</p>
            <h3>3. Add the Vegetables</h3>
            <p>1. Add carrots, cabbage, capsicum, and green chilies to the chicken.
            2. Stir fry for 2–3 minutes (don’t overcook, keep them slightly crunchy).</p>
            <h3>4. Mix Rice and Chicken</h3>
            <p>1. Add the cooked rice to the chicken and vegetables.
            2. Add chopped green onions.
            3. Mix gently so the rice doesn’t break.
            4. Cover and steam on low heat for 10 minutes.</p>
            <h1> Steps</h1>
             <li>Basmati rice – 2 cups  </li>
                <li>Chicken – 300 g (boneless or with bone)  </li>
                   <li>Carrots – 1 (thinly sliced)  </li>
                      <li>Capsicum – 1 (sliced)  </li>
                         <li>Cabbage – 1 cup (shredded)  </li>
                            <li>Green onions – 1/2 cup (chopped)  </li>
                               <li>Green chilies – 2 (slit)  </li>
                                  <li>Garlic – 1 tbsp (chopped)  </li>
                                     <li>Soya sauce – 2 tbsp  </li>
                                        <li>Vinegar – 1 tbsp  </li>
                                           <li>Black pepper – 1 tsp  </li>
                                              <li>Salt – to taste  </li>
                                                 <li>Oil – 3 tbsp  </li>
                                                    <li>Water – 4 cups  </li>
                                                       <li>Chicken cube (optional) – 1 </li>
